t, and as the underlying Scheme engine for executing expressions and programs entered into DrScheme's read-eval-print loop. We describe the key elements of the MrEd virtual machine for building a programming environment, and we step through the implementation of a miniature version of DrScheme in MrEd. More generally, we show how MrEd defines a high-level operating system for graphical programs.</p><p><u>Downloads:</u></p><ul><li><a href="http://www.ccs.neu.edu/scheme/pubs/icfp99-ffkf.pdf">pdf</a></li><li><a href="http://www.ccs.neu.edu/scheme/pubs/icfp99-ffkf.ps.gz">ps</a></li></ul><p><u>Bibtex citation:</u></p><pre>@inproceedings{
